Gregory Govender of Sagekal Logistics made a brief appearance in the Verulam Magistrate's Court on Friday. The case was transferred to the higher court where a trial date will be set.Govender's charges relate to the contravention of the National Road Traffic Act the Immigration Act and operating an unroadworthy vehicle.The driver of the truck Swazi citizen Sanele May was sentenced to eight years imprisonment in November 2014. The truck he was driving crashed into a minibus taxi and several other vehicles on September 5 2013.Govender was not initially charged but it reportedly emerged during May's initial bail application that the truck he was driving was not roadworthy and that May was an illegal immigrant.